    <text type="letter">
        <body>  
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#ht">See notes Dec 6 1888</note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_es.00500.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener> 
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office.</name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>ASYLUM FOR THE INSANE</name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>LONDON.</name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>ONTARIO</name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>London, Ont.,<ptr target="loc.07276_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1888-12-03"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>3 Dec<handShift
                            rend="printed"/> 188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>8</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Your letter of friday &#38; Saturday (30th &#38; 1st)<ptr target="loc.07276_n3"/> came to hand this
                afternoon and has made me feel very anxious for you. I fear you are suffering a
                great deal. I have written to Osler<ptr target="n4302"/> urging him to try and do something to <choice><sic>releive</sic><corr>relieve</corr></choice>
                that horrible irritation of the bladder that keeps you getting up so much at night
                and it seems to me imperative that the bowels should be kept open. I fear that
                    Osler is too busy to give you the attention you require and
                it seems to me that you ought to have him recommend a good man who would see you
                every day, and twice a day if necessary while O. himself<pb xml:id="leaf002v"
                    facs="loc_es.00501.jpg" type="verso"/> would come over from time to time and see
                you with him. I have also written to Traubel<ptr target="n4267"/> urging him to make some arrangement by
                which you will be seen at least once a day by some good doctor&#8212;I wish I could
                be with you but that is impossible at present. I shall hope to hear very soon that
                proper arrangements have been made and that you are more comfortable</p>
            <closer> 
                <salute>I am always</salute>
                <salute>affectionately yours</salute>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_es.00498.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_es.00499.jpg" type="verso"/>
